This paper deals with detecting side-channel attacks in software, which is a topic that falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also focuses on symbolic execution, which is a technique commonly used in software engineering (cs.SE) and programming languages (cs.PL) research. The use of an SMT solver also suggests a connection to the category of systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper deals with cache timing leaks, which is a topic that falls under the category of computer architecture (cs.AR).
